&amp; Radcliffe (
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFD8E9C5F2FDF57AC6" box="[508,530,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3B86FFDB37C5F2FD317AC1" author="Radcliffe, L." box="[546,726,2010,2036]" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" pagination="105 - 140" refId="ref298180" refString="Radcliffe, L. (1912) Description of a new family, two new genera, and twenty-nine new species of anacanthine fishes from the Philippine Islands and contiguous waters. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 43, 105 - 140, pls. 22 - 31. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.43 - 1924.105" type="journal article" year="1912">Radcliffe 1912</bibRefCitation>
). In the key to 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3B86FFD81BC5D4FE647523" authorityName="Gilbert &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1920" box="[270,387,2044,2070]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Lucigadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFD81BC5D4FE647523" box="[270,387,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">Lucigadus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3B86FFDB91C5D4FC0D7B69" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Okamoto, M." box="[644,1002,1601,2070]" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" pagination="369 - 380" refId="ref288830" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Okamoto, M. (2015) A new grenadier fish of the genus Lucigadus (Macrouridae, Gadiformes, Teleostei) from the Emperor Seamounts, northwestern Pacific. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 62, 369 - 380." type="journal article" year="2015">Iwamoto &amp; Okamoto (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3B86FFDAECC46AFB2E7B6E" box="[1017,1225,1602,1627]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Lucigadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigromarginatu">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFDAECC46AFB2E7B6E" box="[1017,1225,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">L. nigromarginatu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3B86FFDA3FC44CFAE17B4B" authority="Iwamoto &amp; Merrett, 1997" authorityName="Iwamoto &amp; Merrett" authorityYear="1997" box="[810,1286,1635,1662]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Lucigadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acrolophus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFDA3FC44CFC2E7B48" box="[810,969,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">L. acrolophus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B297ED8FF3B86FFDAC1C44CFAE17B4B" author="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R." box="[980,1286,1636,1662]" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" pagination="473 - 570" refId="ref288733" refString="Iwamoto, T. &amp; Merrett, N. R. (1997) Pisces Gadiformes: taxonomy of grenadiers of the New Caledonian region, southwest Pacific. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, 176, 473 - 570." type="journal article" year="1997">Iwamoto &amp; Merrett, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. According to their study, 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3B86FFDABEC4AEFB667BAA" box="[939,1153,1670,1695]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Lucigadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigromarginatus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFDABEC4AEFB667BAA" box="[939,1153,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">L. nigromarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F8B878AAFF3B86FFDC07C4AEFA4C7BAA" authorityName="Iwamoto &amp; Merrett" authorityYear="1997" box="[1298,1451,1669,1695]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Lucigadus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="237" pageNumber="238" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acrolophus">
<emphasis id="0DCCDF3BFF3B86FFDC07C4AEFA4C7BAA" box="[1298,1451,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="237" pageNumber="238">L. acrolophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a shorter snout (24–28% HL vs. 28–32%), a lower first dorsal fin (92–107% HL vs. 108–129%), an apical black spot on the first dorsal fin (vs. anterior third of the fin membrane blackish), and a blackish anterodistal margin of the anal fin (vs. absent).
</paragraph>
